<Author>metalrat
<Content>Exceptional value and service I have stayed at the Bishop Lei twice, most recently in October, 2006. Though the rooms are compact, they are clean, well appointed and exceptional value --and besides, did you travel to Hong Kong to stay inside? Unless you are travelling with kids or in a group, there is plenty of room. Do you really want to pay three times as much just to have 30 extra square feet?Harbour view rooms provide an exceptional view of Central. Watch Hong Kong' s nightly light show from the comfort of your room, the terrace outside the coffee shop or my favourite spot, while you're in the pool! Wireless internet is free in rooms, though there is a charge for internet access in the business centre. The concierge, housekeeping and deskstaff are all helpful. Location is great -- a few minutes walk from the escalators and ess than a half an hour stroll down to the Star Ferry --or hop in a cab for about $30 HKD (luggage is extra) . My only requests would include bathtubs (though the showers are great) and extended hours for the pool which could be open a little earlier and later --especially during the hotter months. I will never stay anywhere else in Hong Kong. 
