<Author>chos
<Content>Great Stay My partner and I stayed here at the end of May. The hotel is up the mountain a bit, but is two blocks from Central-mid-levels escalator, so it was pretty convenient. It's not cheap, but seems like a good deal for Hong Kong -- and for being so accessible Central.The room, bathroom, and sheets were quite clean, though the air smelled a little musty when we arrived. The windows do not open. While we had control over the A/C, it was hard to regulate, so we were often too warm or too cold. The bathroom was fairly small and had a standing shower (no tub.) We did not try the breakfast.It was nice to have a pool, though the pool is not as big as it seems on the Web site.Staff were very accomodating when our flight changed, and we had to come back after checking out.Overall, our stay was comfortable and a good deal, though we might look around for something more special the next time we're in town. 
