<Author>Lost_N_Translation
<Content>Price/Location combo make this place unbeatable Let me preface this review by saying that I am a resident of Hong Kong, and in fact own a flat on Robinson Road. During the renovations of our flat, we were frequent guests at the Bishop Lei as it about 2 blocks from our flat. Let me also say that this is not normally the type of hotel I'd consider - I'm ridiculously picky.Having said all of that, I challenge you to find a hotel in Hong Kong that is more conveniently located for the prices they charge. Yes, you have to step outside to change your mind in the small rooms. Yes, they're basic. But they're clean, comfortable, and for $500HKD/night ($65US) you cannot touch it anywhere else in Hong Kong. And besides, if you're doing much more than sleeping in the room, you've missed the point of a visit to Hong Kong.Just one other note to refute a prior review - while it's true that they do not provide bottled water in the rooms, it is in fact untrue that the water isn't potable. Tap water is perfectly safe in Hong Kong. 
